ands town not even counting its better effect but 22 dmg 43 delay is a lot better than 20dmg, 42 delay at least in my version of Everquest.  That means that Shamans probably have a better version 2h blunt than the Gardash maul in the POH, so there.<BR>I think the reason they seperated these mega weapons between troll/ogre and barbarian is that Shamanism is just a crude science by the trolls and ogres whereas a barbarian shaman embraces shamanism since they tap a connection tooo animal spirits.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Nadger</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">all 3 races are the same damn class.  Babrarians have more base wisdom.  Trolls/ogres are better at melee.  Troll have regen, ogre have strength, barb have about 20 more mana.<P>The gardash is comparable to the spiritists hammer.  Because while we are averaging for 70 damage or so with it.  Your hitting for about 40 damage with your spiritists hammer.  Your proc goes off maybe once a fight.  By the time your proc goes off the troll/ogre has done more melee damage then your proc combined with your melee damage.  The proc isnt allways going to do full damage, and it going to be resisted some times too.  And it may not even go off.<P>The gardash mauls delay can be buffed down to about 35 delay with aleracy.<P>It dosnt really matter much anyway.  Most of the time high level shamans arent meleeing, we are doting, buffing, debuffing, nuking, and meditating.<P>So the gardashs +15 wisdom is better there.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Chilipepa</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Im interested in this spiritist hammer. I am a barbarian shaman. What level is Cazic Thule and where do I find him? Does he just drop it when you kill him?<P>Chilipepa<BR>12th season<BR>Mathaniel Marr</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Vooda</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZ